# SIE Exam Tutor — Content Outline & Context

Use this rule when building or editing **SIE (Securities Industry Essentials)** practice content, questions, explanations, or Coach UI copy. It reflects the FINRA SIE content outline so questions and feedback stay aligned with the real exam.

## Exam Specs

- **Questions:** 75 multiple-choice
- **Time:** 1 hour 45 minutes
- **Passing score:** 70%
- **Eligibility:** Open to all; co-requisite for Series 57
- **Sections:** 4 (per FINRA outline below)

---

## Section 1: Knowledge of Capital Markets (16%, 12 questions)

**Focus:** Market structure, regulators, participants, economic factors.

### Regulatory entities

- **SEC** — Enforces federal securities laws
- **FINRA / SROs** — Self-regulation (e.g., rules on options trading)
- **State regulators (NASAA)** — Blue sky laws
- **Federal Reserve** — Monetary policy (e.g., impact on margin borrowing, volatility)
- **SIPC / FDIC** — Investor protection

### Market participants

- Investors (retail), Broker-Dealers, Issuers, Underwriters, Market Makers

### Market types

- **Primary** — New issues
- **Secondary** — Exchanges (e.g., NASDAQ)
- **Third / Fourth** — Institutional, dark pools

### Economic factors

- Fed rates (margin borrowing, LEAPs financing)
- Business cycles, inflation (e.g., impact on options premiums)

---

## Section 2: Understanding Products and Their Risks (44%, 33 questions)

**Focus:** Securities types, features, risks. High weight; options matter for Series 57 prep.

### Equity securities

- Common stock (voting, dividends), Preferred (fixed dividends)
- Risks: Market, volatility

### Debt securities

- Corporate bonds, yields (inverse to price)
- Risks: Interest rate, credit

### Packaged products

- Mutual funds, ETFs, REITs
- Risks: Liquidity, fees

### Options

- Calls/puts; Greeks (e.g., delta); strategies (covered calls, wheel, spreads, straddles)
- Risks: Time decay (theta), unlimited loss for naked sellers
- Multi-leg: Spreads, straddles for risk management

### Other

- Annuities, alternatives (e.g., hedge funds)

---

## Section 3: Trading, Customer Accounts & Prohibited Activities (31%, 23 questions)

**Focus:** Trading mechanics, account types, ethics.

### Trading

- Order types (market, limit), NBBO, settlement (e.g., T+1 for equities)

### Customer accounts

- Cash, Margin (e.g., borrow for LEAPs), Retirement (IRAs)

### Returns

- Capital gains, dividends, interest

### Prohibited activities

- Insider trading, manipulation (pump/dump), front-running
- Compliance: Suitability (e.g., for aggressive strategies)

---

## Section 4: Overview of the Regulatory Framework (9%, 7 questions)

**Focus:** Registration, ethics, reporting.

- **Registration:** Form U4, continuing education
- **Ethics:** Gifts, conflicts of interest (e.g., recommending high-risk options)
- **Reporting:** SARs, complaint handling

---

## How to Use This Rule

- **Writing SIE questions:** Tag or align questions to one of the four sections and topics above; keep explanations accurate and concise.
- **Explanations / feedback:** Reference correct regulatory or product terms (e.g., FINRA, SIPC, theta, NBBO) where relevant.
- **Coach UI / copy:** When mentioning SIE format, use 75 questions, 1 hr 45 min, 70% pass; section weights can inform “weak area” or topic labels.
- **Study tips in-app:** Time (e.g., 20–30 hours over 2 weeks), mocks (75-question format), formulas (e.g., options breakeven), FINRA outline and practice exams.
